---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Water Crisis"
  description="400 million people in Sub-Saharan Africa lack safe water. The crisis across East Africa: health, gender, prices, infrastructure, and water efficiency."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="hero-badge">Understanding the Crisis</div>
    <h1>The Water <em>Crisis</em></h1>
    <p>Sub-Saharan Africa carries the world's heaviest water burden. The facts are stark.</p>
    <svg class="hero-wave" viewBox="0 0 1440 100" preserveAspectRatio="none">
      <path d="M0,60 C360,100 720,20 1080,60 C1260,80 1380,50 1440,60 L1440,100 L0,100Z" fill="white"/>
    </svg>
  </section>

  <!-- Global Stats -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">The Scale</div>
      <div class="section-title">A Crisis Hiding in Plain Sight</div>

      <div class="stat-grid fade-in">
        <div class="stat-card large">
          <span class="stat-value">400M+</span>
          <span class="stat-label">People in Sub-Saharan Africa lack safe drinking water</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-value">6+ hrs</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Daily water collection time for women in rural East Africa</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-value">10x</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Price gap: Kibera households versus Karen households</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-value">297K</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Children under 5 die annually from waterborne disease in Africa</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- East Africa -->
  <section class="bg-sand">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">East Africa</div>
      <div class="section-title">The Region at the Heart of the Crisis</div>
      <div class="crisis-grid fade-in">
        <div class="crisis-visual">
          <img src="/women-carrying-water-jerrycans-kenya.png" alt="Women in Kenya carrying jerrycans of water on their backs, the daily burden of water collection across East Africa" loading="lazy" width="800" height="600" />
          <div class="overlay">
            <p>Women and girls walk hours every day to collect water instead of attending school or earning a living.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="crisis-facts">
          <div class="crisis-fact">
            <div class="icon">◈</div>
            <div>
              <h4>Lowest Access Rates Globally</h4>
              <p>Sub-Saharan Africa has the lowest safe water access of any region. Some rural communities have none.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="crisis-fact">
            <div class="icon">◇</div>
            <div>
              <h4>Women Bear the Burden</h4>
              <p>Women and girls walk 6+ km daily for water, sacrificing education, income, and safety.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="crisis-fact">
            <div class="icon">◆</div>
            <div>
              <h4>Preventable Disease</h4>
              <p>Cholera, typhoid, and diarrhoea from contaminated water kill children under 5 every day.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="crisis-fact">
            <div class="icon">◉</div>
            <div>
              <h4>Economies Held Back</h4>
              <p>The African Development Bank estimates water insecurity costs the continent billions annually.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Urban Crisis -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">The Urban Crisis</div>
      <div class="section-title">Even in Nairobi, Millions Are Failed</div>

      <div class="urban-grid fade-in">
        <div class="urban-card has-image">
          <img src="/boda-carrying-water.png" alt="A boda boda rider in Nairobi delivering jerrycans of water, a common sight in informal water vendor networks across Kenyan cities" loading="lazy" width="600" height="400" />
          <h3>Informal Vendors</h3>
          <p>Millions in Nairobi, Kampala, and Dar es Salaam depend on unregulated, untested, overpriced water vendors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="urban-card has-image">
          <img src="/longqueue-water-lines.png" alt="A long queue of residents waiting at a water collection point in Kenya holding jerrycans, the daily reality of urban water scarcity" loading="lazy" width="600" height="400" />
          <h3>Price Exploitation</h3>
          <p>Low-income estates pay up to 10x more per litre than wealthy neighbourhoods on municipal supply.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="urban-card has-image">
          <img src="/unsafe-tap-nairobi-water-urban-areas-apartments-homes-dirty-water.png" alt="Discoloured unsafe tap water in a Nairobi apartment showing the contamination risk in urban Kenyan homes" loading="lazy" width="600" height="400" />
          <h3>Unknown Quality</h3>
          <p>Most water sources are never tested. No labels, no accountability. <a href="/majimap/">MajiMap</a> closes that gap.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="price-callout fade-in">
        <div class="callout-inner">
          <h3>"Why does water cost 10x more in Kibera than in Karen?"</h3>
          <p>The question that launched <a href="/majimap/">MajiMap</a>, our public data platform for water pricing, quality, and access.</p>
          <a href="/majimap/" class="btn btn-primary">Explore MajiMap &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Country Breakdown -->
  <section class="focus-section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">Country by Country</div>
      <div class="section-title">The Crisis Across East Africa</div>
      <div class="country-breakdown fade-in">
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇰🇪</span>
          <h4>Kenya</h4>
          <p>28 million lack safe water. Nairobi's utility serves less than half the city.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇺🇬</span>
          <h4>Uganda</h4>
          <p>21 million without basic water access. Kampala mirrors Nairobi's pricing inequality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇪🇹</span>
          <h4>Ethiopia</h4>
          <p>The largest water-insecure population in East Africa. Drought cycles are accelerating.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇹🇿</span>
          <h4>Tanzania</h4>
          <p>24 million without clean water. Dar es Salaam's growth outpaces infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇸🇴</span>
          <h4>Somalia</h4>
          <p>Conflict has devastated infrastructure. One of the most water-stressed nations on earth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇷🇼</span>
          <h4>Rwanda</h4>
          <p>3 million Rwandans still lack safe water despite strong governance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="country-card">
          <span class="country-flag">🇧🇮</span>
          <h4>Burundi</h4>
          <p>Only 1 in 4 rural Burundians has access to a basic water source.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Water Efficiency -->
  <section class="bg-sand">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-label">The Efficiency Crisis</div>
      <div class="section-title">Africa's Water Isn't Just Scarce. It's Wasted.</div>

      <div class="efficiency-stats fade-in">
        <div class="eff-stat">
          <span class="eff-value">50%</span>
          <span class="eff-label">Of rural water points break within 5 years of installation (RWSN, 2021)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-stat">
          <span class="eff-value">6%</span>
          <span class="eff-label">Of African cropland is irrigated, versus 37% in Asia (FAO AQUASTAT)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-stat">
          <span class="eff-value">40%</span>
          <span class="eff-label">Of urban water is lost to leakage and theft across Africa (UN-Water JMP)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-stat">
          <span class="eff-value">$30B</span>
          <span class="eff-label">Annual cost of water insecurity to African economies (World Bank, 2022)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="efficiency-grid fade-in">
        <div class="eff-card has-image">
          <img src="/Dam-dry-pipes-kenya-water-system.png" alt="A dry dam and broken water pipes in rural Kenya, illustrating rural water infrastructure failure across Sub-Saharan Africa" loading="lazy" width="600" height="400" />
          <h3>Rural Infrastructure Failure</h3>
          <p>50,000+ rural water points in Sub-Saharan Africa are broken at any time (RWSN). The problem is maintenance, not construction. Without local technical capacity and spare parts, expensive infrastructure becomes scrap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-card">
          <div class="eff-icon">▢</div>
          <h3>Agriculture &amp; Irrigation</h3>
          <p>Africa has 60% of the world's uncultivated arable land but irrigates only 6% (FAO). Crop water productivity is 2 to 4 times lower than global averages. Better water management could double yields.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-card">
          <div class="eff-icon">◫</div>
          <h3>Urban Water Management</h3>
          <p>Non-revenue water averages 40% across African cities (IWA). Nairobi loses an estimated 42% of treated water before it reaches customers. Residents pay more for less.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eff-card has-image">
          <img src="/kenya-floods-droughts-water-stress-climate.png" alt="Split image showing flooded streets and cracked drought-stricken earth in Kenya, the climate water stress paradox" loading="lazy" width="600" height="400" />
          <h3>Water Stress &amp; Climate</h3>
          <p>The WRI Aqueduct tool classifies 25 African countries as high or extremely high water stress by 2040. East Africa has abundant rainfall but insufficient capture and storage. The Horn of Africa just endured its worst drought in 40 years.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="efficiency-callout fade-in">
        <div class="eff-callout-inner">
          <h3>Water efficiency is the multiplier</h3>
          <p>Every litre saved through better infrastructure, smarter agriculture, and reduced urban waste reaches someone who needs it. MiMaji Foundation combines <a href="/majimap/">data visibility</a> with the <a href="https://mimaji.co.ke" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MiMaji platform</a> to close efficiency gaps in Nairobi.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="section-title">The Crisis Is Urgent.<br>The Solution Is Within Reach.</div>
    <p>Clean water technology exists. The data is clear. What's needed now is action from partners, donors, volunteers, and communities.</p>
    <div class="cta-buttons">
      <a href="/take-action/" class="btn btn-white">Take Action &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/majimap/" class="btn btn-outline">Explore MajiMap</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .stat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .stat-card {
    background: var(--sand);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .stat-card.large {
    grid-column: span 1;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--blue-deep) 0%, var(--blue) 100%);
    color: var(--white);
    border: none;
  }

  .stat-card.large .stat-label {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }

  .stat-value {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  .stat-card.large .stat-value {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 3rem;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .urban-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .urban-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--white);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .urban-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(10, 94, 181, 0.1);
  }

  .urban-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .urban-card.has-image {
    padding: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .urban-card.has-image img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16/10;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .urban-card.has-image h3,
  .urban-card.has-image p {
    padding-left: 1.8rem;
    padding-right: 1.8rem;
  }

  .urban-card.has-image h3 {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
  }

  .urban-card.has-image p {
    padding-bottom: 1.8rem;
  }

  .urban-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--blue-deep);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .urban-card p {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .urban-card a {
    color: var(--blue);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .price-callout {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .callout-inner {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--blue-deep), var(--blue));
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .callout-inner h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .callout-inner p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    max-width: 550px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .callout-inner a {
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  .country-breakdown {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .country-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 14px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .country-card:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  .country-flag {
    font-size: 2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .country-card h4 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .country-card p {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .stat-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .urban-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .country-breakdown {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .stat-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .stat-card.large {
      grid-column: span 1;
    }
  }

  /* Water Efficiency */
  .efficiency-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eff-stat {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 14px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--white);
  }

  .eff-value {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    color: var(--blue);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .eff-label {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .efficiency-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .eff-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--white);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  .eff-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(10, 94, 181, 0.1);
  }

  .eff-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .eff-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--blue-deep);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .eff-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .eff-card.has-image {
    padding: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .eff-card.has-image img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16/10;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .eff-card.has-image h3,
  .eff-card.has-image p {
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .eff-card.has-image h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .eff-card.has-image p {
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .efficiency-callout {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .eff-callout-inner {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--teal), var(--blue));
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .eff-callout-inner h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .eff-callout-inner p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .eff-callout-inner a {
    color: var(--gold);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .efficiency-stats {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }

    .efficiency-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .efficiency-stats {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
